Betty,<br><br>
Thanks for the input.  This is a good summation of what's been happening on this thread.<br><br>
Please note, everyone, that when I picked the name &quot;Betty&quot; out of the air I wasn't thinking of our &quot;Betty&quot; (the one above) but of an adopted Korean gal I knew from the 1960's.  <br><br>
Concerning Doc Del, he has had some very traumatic experiences, in Vietnam and just recently, and like me feels that even subtile racism needs to be confronted.  If we can, the ultimate aim is to change behavior/attitudes so that our loved ones don't have to put up with the @$@$ we've experienced.  <br><br>
When I was a scuba diving instructor, we were taught that we teach as if we were instructing our own loved ones.  If our instruction didn't meet that standard (&quot;Would I let this person teach my daughter haw to dive?&quot;) we were not passed as instructors.  <br><br>
This is the standard I think Doc Del and I have.  It is very personal, but pertainent to the world we wish our kids to inherit.  When I saw the postings to Lien, I asked myself if I would wish this kind of response on my omn child.  <br><br>
Again, thanks for the summary.<br><br>

